        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): reset finalize retry transcript",
        "body": "Closes #93166.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n`before_agent_finalize` retries could leave the rejected first assistant answer as finalized session history before the revision pass, so group-chat silence handling could collapse final delivery.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nWhen a finalize revision is honored, the runner now trims the just-produced assistant leaf from the session transcript before dispatching the retry. The revision pass remains authoritative, including intentional `NO_REPLY`, and the rejected first answer is not restored.\n\n## User Impact\nHook-driven revisions no longer make the retry model see its own rejected draft as prior conversation, avoiding the silent response drop and duplicate transcript sequence.\n\n## Evidence\nFocused runner coverage now simulates a visible first pass followed by both revised and silent retry outcomes. The touched runner tests passed after rebase, and the core typecheck passed locally.",
        "branch": "fix-93166-finalize-retry-transcript",
